<paragraph id="8BDA369DFFC4B46FFF02B2BCFCABFE06" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B2BCFEC7FF1A" box="[199,361,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Measurements</emphasis>
(mm). Male / female. Body length: 1.84/1.94±0.01; head length: 0.50/0.51±0.02; head width: 0.41/0.50±0.05; eye width: 0.11/0.10±0.01; interocular space: 0.21/0.24±0.01; interocellar space: 0.16/0.18; preocellar distance: 0.03/0.03; labium: I 0.04/0.05±0.01, II 0.04/0.05±0.01, III 0.46/0.48±0.03, IV 0.32/0.28±0.08; antennomeres: I 0.20/0.23±0.03; II 0.16/0.15±0.01; III 0.20/0.20±0.01; IVa 0.16/0.16±0.01; IVb 0.18/0.20±0.03;pronotum length: 0.46/0.45±0.01; humeral width: 0.52/0.84±0.01; metanotal elevation length: 0.25/0.25±0.01; metanotal elevation width: 0.41/0.44±0.01; abdomen with hemelytra length: 1.00/0.90±0.15; abdomen without hemelytra length: 1.00/0.90±0.15; abdominal width: 0.66/0.77±0.03; length of metafemur: 0.50/0.52±0.01, metatibia: 0.64/0.62±0.01, metatarsus: 0.22/ 0.24±0.01.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA369DFFC4B46FFF02B392FBD0FE7A" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,933]" box="[199,1150,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B392FE91FE7A" bold="true" box="[199,319,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Variation.</emphasis>
Without evident sexual dimorphism although the female is slightly larger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6516FFC4B46FFF02B3F9FD93FCF7" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA369DFFC4B46FFF02B3F9FBC4FD2F" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B3F9FD5DFE5F" bold="true" box="[199,755,476,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Differential diagnosis and comparatives notes.</emphasis>
Body size between 1.84 and 
<quantity id="4C9D9B78FFC4B46FFB86B3F9FB02FE5E" box="[1091,1196,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" unit="mm" value="1.95">1.95 mm</quantity>
. Bucculae yellowish, ventrally curved, posteriorly conically produced and slightly elevated. Clavus with a pearl-white marking and four whitish spots on the membrane. Metanotal elevation short triangular, without any incision; with raised edges and strong, straight median carina. Male genitalia: pygophore elliptical; paramere hook-shaped, with long setae apically, short setae in the medially, basal region robust, apical end robust and rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA369DFFC4B46FFF02B0B5FD93FCF7" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFF02B0B5FE31FD02" authority="Stella &amp; Pall, 2018" authorityName="Stella &amp; Pall" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,415,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alvearensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B0B5FE31FD02" box="[199,415,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Hebrus alvearensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257F4FFC4B46FFE63B0AAFDAEFD02" box="[422,512,655,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFE63B0AAFDAEFD02" bold="true" box="[422,512,655,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is approximately the same size as 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFC42B0B5FA9CFD02" authority="Drake &amp; Harris, 1943" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1943" box="[903,1330,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="priscus">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFC42B0B5FB9CFD0D" box="[903,1074,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Hebrus priscus</emphasis>
Drake &amp; Harris, 1943
</taxonomicName>
, which is known from Cuyaba, 
<collectingCountry id="F372760DFFC4B46FFE4AB091FE7BFD67" box="[399,469,692,717]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Brasil</collectingCountry>
. The latter can be easily distinguished because the apex of the metanotal elevation is forked, there are no pale spots on the membrane or pearly-white markings at the clavus, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFB3EB0FCFA35FD5A" authorityName="Stella &amp; Pall" authorityYear="2018" box="[1275,1435,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alvearensis">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFB3EB0FCFA35FD5A" box="[1275,1435,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">H. alvearensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the metanotal elevation is posteriorly rounded without any incision and there are spots on the membrane and clavus. In addition, the disc of metanotal elevation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFCC7B104FC0BFC92" authorityName="Stella &amp; Pall" authorityYear="2018" box="[770,933,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alvearensis">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFCC7B104FC0BFC92" box="[770,933,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">H. alvearensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a straight median carina, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFA44B104FF46FCF6" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="priscus">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFA44B104FF46FCF6" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">H. priscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is imperceptible and dotted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6516FFC4B46FFF02B14DFC09FC0F" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA369DFFC4B46FFF02B14DFC09FC0F" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFF02B14DFE2EFC2A" authorityName="Drake and Chapman" authorityYear="1958" box="[199,384,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="engaeus">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B14DFE2EFC2A" box="[199,384,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Hebrus engaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only congener known in 
<collectingCountry id="F372760DFFC4B46FFD23B142FCF6FC2A" box="[742,856,871,896]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, has important differences with 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFB11B14CFAD6FC2A" authorityName="Stella &amp; Pall" authorityYear="2018" box="[1236,1400,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alvearensis">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFB11B14CFAD6FC2A" box="[1236,1400,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">H. alvearensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs specifically in the following unique combination of characters:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6516FFC4B46FFF02B4D0FC24F898" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDA369DFFC4B46FFF02B4D0FC24F898" blockId="3.[199,1394,1781,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B4D0FEE0F8A4" bold="true" box="[199,334,1781,1806]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1EFFC4B46FFDFDB4D0FD19F8A7" authorityName="Stella &amp; Pall" authorityYear="2018" box="[568,695,1781,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alvearensis">
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFDFDB4D0FD19F8A7" box="[568,695,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">alvearensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the name of the city where the species was collected. 
<emphasis id="B911EA8FFFC4B46FFF02B53CFECEF898" bold="true" box="[199,352,1817,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F372760DFFC4B46FFEA2B53CFE75F898" box="[359,475,1817,1842]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Argentina</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49A1F87FFFC4B46FFE20B53FFDF5F89B" box="[485,603,1818,1841]" country="Argentina" name="La Pampa" pageId="3" pageNumber="477">La Pampa</collectingRegion>
: Intendente Alvear (
<figureCitation id="135E2A18FFC4B46FFCFBB53CFCD3F898" box="[830,893,1817,1842]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,821,843]" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distribution of species of Hebrus in Argentina." pageId="3" pageNumber="477">Fig.6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
